On the other hand, the main limiting factor in excitonic solar cells is the exciton diffusion length.39,40 The exciton cannot dissociate at the same location at which it was generated. Rather, it has to travel by hopping to the nearest interface to dissociate. Thus, the transport is limited by exciton diffusion rather than the free carrier diffusion. Exciton diffusion length in organic solar cell materials is normally <0.1 μm.19–21 In this work, we assume the following values for Ld as characteristic for the following material families:
for indirect-gap semiconductors, Ld≈200 μm,
for direct-gap semiconductors, Ld≈10 μm,
for organometallic semiconductors, Ld≈0.6 μm,
for excitonic cells, Ld≈0.1 μm.
